WHAT ARE MAGIC TABLES IN SQL SERVER? Magic tables are the temporary logical tables that are created by the SQL server whenever there are insertion or deletion or update( D.M.L) operations. Types of magic tables: INSERTED â€“ The recently inserted row gets added to the
INSERTED magic table. DELETED â€“ The recently deleted row gets added to the DELETED magic table. The use of magic tables are TRIGGERS.

