////////////////////////////////////////////////86>
1. SP may or may not return a value, but Function must return a value
ðŸ”¸ Stored Procedure Example:
CREATE PROCEDURE sp_GetEmployee
AS
BEGIN
    SELECT * FROM Employees; -- No return needed
END
âœ… Here, it just performs an action, doesn't return any single value.

ðŸ”¹ Function Example:
CREATE FUNCTION fn_GetTotalSalary()
RETURNS INT
AS
BEGIN
    DECLARE @total INT;
    SELECT @total = SUM(Salary) FROM Employees;
    RETURN @total;
END
âœ… Function must return a value (here: total salary).

2. SP can have input/output parameters, Function only has input parameters
ðŸ”¸ Stored Procedure with Output:
CREATE PROCEDURE sp_GetEmployeeCount
    @DeptId INT,
    @Count INT OUTPUT
AS
BEGIN
    SELECT @Count = COUNT(*) FROM Employees WHERE DepartmentId = @DeptId;
END
ðŸ”¹ Function can only have input:
CREATE FUNCTION fn_GetDeptSalary(@DeptId INT)
RETURNS INT
AS
BEGIN
    DECLARE @salary INT;
    SELECT @salary = SUM(Salary) FROM Employees WHERE DepartmentId = @DeptId;
    RETURN @salary;
END
âŒ You cannot use OUTPUT parameters in a function.

3. We can call a Function inside a SP, but cannot call SP inside a Function
âœ… Call function inside SP:
CREATE PROCEDURE sp_ShowSalary
AS
BEGIN
    DECLARE @total INT;
    SET @total = dbo.fn_GetTotalSalary(); -- calling function
    PRINT @total;
END
âŒ Cannot do this in function:
-- INVALID:
-- You cannot write this inside a FUNCTION

-- EXEC sp_GetEmployee; -- âŒ Not allowed inside a function
4. Cannot use SP in SELECT/INSERT/UPDATE â€” but can use Function
âŒ SP cannot be used:
-- INVALID:
SELECT *, sp_GetEmployee() FROM Employees; -- âŒ Error
âœ… Function can be used:
-- Valid:
SELECT Name, dbo.fn_GetDeptSalary(DepartmentId) AS TotalDeptSalary FROM Employees;
âœ… Functions can be used inside SELECT, WHERE, JOIN, etc.

5. TRY-CATCH works in SP, not in Function
âœ… TRY-CATCH in SP:
CREATE PROCEDURE sp_TryCatchDemo
AS
BEGIN
    BEGIN TRY
        SELECT 1 / 0; -- Will cause error
    END TRY
    BEGIN CATCH
        PRINT 'Error occurred!';
    END CATCH
END
âŒ NOT allowed in Function:
-- TRY-CATCH is not allowed inside a FUNCTION in SQL Server
6. Transactions possible in SP, not in Function
âœ… SP with transaction:
CREATE PROCEDURE sp_UpdateSalary
AS
BEGIN
    BEGIN TRANSACTION
        UPDATE Employees SET Salary = Salary + 1000;
    COMMIT TRANSACTION
END
âŒ Transactions NOT allowed in function:
-- BEGIN TRAN / COMMIT TRAN are not allowed inside FUNCTION
ðŸ”š Summary Table:
Feature	Stored Procedure (SP)	Function
Return Value	Optional	Must return something
Parameters	Input + Output	Input only
Callable from SQL query	âŒ No	âœ… Yes
Use in SELECT/UPDATE/DELETE	âŒ No	âœ… Yes
Use inside Function	âŒ No	âœ… Function only
TRY-CATCH / Transactions	âœ… Yes	âŒ No


